@rlevas: We need a consistent hash function for generating fixed length UUID (16-byte). Based on google forums Murmur3Hash is actually faster and produces a 32-bit hash. Since the algorithm is pluggable we are considering a switch with some more testing after this patch. Since the UUID is not exposed to the outside world by AMS and API is protected SPnego we should be alright in terms of security concerns.
